---
layout: base.njk
pageTitle: Registered Devices
permalink: /demo/auth/devices/
tourSteps:
  - selector: "[data-add-device]"
    title: "Add a new device"
    body: "Hōzō supports laptops, phones, USB security keys — anything that speaks WebAuthn."
    next: "/demo/restore/"
---

<div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-6">
  <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold">Registered Devices</h1>
  <a href="/demo/auth/register/"
     data-add-device
     class="btn-primary text-xs px-4 py-2 rounded text-white cursor-pointer">
    + Add Device
  </a>
</div>

<div class="space-y-3">
  {% for cred in devices %}
  <div class="card p-4 flex items-center justify-between">
    <div>
      <div class="font-medium text-sm">{{ cred.device_name }}</div>
      <div class="text-slate-500 text-xs mt-0.5">
        Added {{ cred.added_at | truncate(10, true, "") }} &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        Sign count: {{ cred.sign_count }}
      </div>
      <div class="text-slate-600 text-xs font-mono mt-0.5 truncate max-w-xs">
        id: {{ cred.id | truncate(20, true, "") }}…
      </div>
    </div>
    <button onclick="hozoToast('(demo) Would remove this passkey', 'warn'); return false;"
            class="btn-danger text-xs px-3 py-1.5 rounded text-white cursor-pointer">
      Remove
    </button>
  </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>

{# ── Why passkeys only? ─────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<div class="mt-8 card p-5 border-l-4 border-green-500">
  <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-slate-100 mb-3">🔐 Why passkeys only?</h2>
  <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
    <div>
      <p class="text-slate-200">
        <strong>No passwords.</strong>
        <span class="text-slate-400">
          Nothing to phish, nothing to leak in a breach, nothing to forget.
        </span>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="text-slate-200">
        <strong>No shared secrets on the wire.</strong>
        <span class="text-slate-400">
          WebAuthn uses public-key cryptography — the private key never leaves your device.
        </span>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="text-slate-200">
        <strong>Phishing-resistant by design.</strong>
        <span class="text-slate-400">
          A passkey registered for <code class="text-slate-300">hozo.tailnet.ts.net</code> will
          refuse to sign for any other origin. A look-alike domain cannot impersonate Hōzō to you.
        </span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

{# ── Recovery note ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<div class="mt-4 card p-4 text-xs text-slate-500">
  <strong class="text-slate-400">Recovery tip:</strong>
  Always keep at least 2 registered devices (e.g. laptop + YubiKey) so you
  can recover if one is lost. If you remove all devices, Hōzō enters bootstrap
  mode and anyone on the network can register a new device.
</div>
